doctype5
html
	head
		meta(http-equiv="Content-Type", content="text/html; charset=utf-8")
		meta(property="og:image", content="http://fitztrev.github.io/img/shuttle-logo.png")
		link(rel="stylesheet", type="text/css", href="css/shuttle.css") 
		link(rel="stylesheet", type="text/css", href="http://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Francois+One") 
		title Shuttle | {{ site.tagline }}
	body
		div.container
			div.row
				div.col-lg-6.col-sm-6
					h1 Shuttle
					p.lead
						| {{ site.tagline }}
					br
					br
					div.text-center
						p
							a.btn.btn-block.btn-success.btn-large(href="#")
								i.glyphicon.glyphicon-arrow-down
								| &nbsp; Download Shuttle
						p.text-muted
							em
								| &mdash; or &mdash;
						p
							a(href="https://github.com/fitztrev/shuttle")
								| View on Github
				div.col-lg-6.col-sm-6
					img.pull-right.img-responsive.hidden-sm(src="img/shuttle-logo.png", alt="Shuttle")

			hr

			div.animation
				img.img-responsive(src="http://placehold.it/600x400", alt="How it works")

			hr

			div.row
				div.col-lg-6.col-sm-6
					h3 Configuration
					ol
						li Open the app
						li
							| Edit the contents of 
							code ~/.shuttle-hosts.json
						li Define the menu items and the actions that are run when clicked

					hr

					h3 About
					p
						| Shuttle was created by 
						a(href="http://trevorfitzgerald.com") Trevor Fitzgerald
						| .
					p It does exactly what you see above and nothing more.

					hr.visible-sm

				div.col-lg-6.col-sm-6

					h3 FAQs
					hr

					h4 What terminal programs are supported?
					p
						| By default, it uses Terminal.app. To switch it to iTerm2, edit 
						code ~/.shuttle.plist
						|  and change the terminal application value.
					hr

					h4 Why is the config a JSON file?
					p Keep your config in Dropbox or under version control (preferrably private) and you can have it synced across multiple computers.
					p Also, it makes it easy to generate a dynamic list of hosts from your hosting provider (if they have an API), so you're always up-to-date.
